[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man accused of attempting to murder 11 people

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has gone on trial accused of attempting to murder 11 people, including members of his family.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident is said to have occurred at a holiday home in the Highlands on 27 October 2015.
Kieran Ridley, 32, from Worcester in the West Midlands, is alleged to have poured petrol on a kitchen floor.
He is then said to have opened gas valves and set light to a refuse bin before locking doors and windows at the house at Mallaig Mhor, Mallaig.
The indictment at the High Court in Livingston said he tried to kill his mother Ann, his brother Duncan and others, including four children.
Mr Ridley is charged with assaulting the occupants of the house to the danger of their lives and attempting to murder them.
At the time of the incident, the people in the house were reported to have escaped without serious injury.
